  "notes": "Scottish Gaelic (Gàidhlig). ~57,000 speakers (2011 census). Highlands and Islands of Scotland. Pre-aspiration of voiceless stops (diagnostic feature vs. Irish). Broad/slender distinction as in Irish. Lenition system similar to Irish. Substrate of Scottish English (/x/ in 'loch'). Refs: Ó Baoill (2010), Gillies (2009).",
